# Build-context ignore for the repo-root context used by every prod image
# (docker-compose.prod.yml builds with context: . and -f infra/docker/<name>.Dockerfile).
# Docker/BuildKit reads .dockerignore from the CONTEXT ROOT, so it must live here —
# an infra/.dockerignore would never be applied. Keeps node_modules / build outputs /
# secrets out of the context sent to the daemon.

**/node_modules
**/.next
**/dist
**/.turbo
**/.swc
**/coverage
**/*.tsbuildinfo

.git
.github
.vscode
.idea

# secrets / local env (templates in infra/env are NOT ignored)
.env
.env.*
!infra/env/.env.prod.example
!infra/env/.env.example

# docs / assets not needed by any build
docs
*.md
*.log
hostero_logo.png
**/.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
